<p>The US military carried out a strike in the Caribbean Sea on Saturday that killed three people, US defence secretary Pete Hegseth said; he told reporters the vessel was operated by a US‑designated terrorist organisation but did not name the group . Al Jazeera reports Hegseth said the operation was carried out on the orders of President Trump and described the target as &quot;narco-terrorists&quot; . The operation is the latest in a series of maritime actions that, according to one report, have brought the toll from US strikes in the region to at least 64 people, and it has drawn criticism from the United Nations and other countries .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/9sPd_KspvxPqI3HerEDPguF9mNLySa6ycJoC8dISMyBVSqrSZdbuyCerbyQ21RzMUjpTrAuZJV8Po2QFPxm1tm9yZmhPu8AYU4S-WQUiSqkFm8jyQ2M8swhCdusp62iUnDu7RI6pz7odi_A_rKPxR1jIYo36OV1txif2PKxK4XG4' alt='US Defence Secretary Pete Hegseth, who announced the strike on social media' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Cumulative toll: One report says this strike is part of a campaign that has killed at least 64 people in US strikes in the Caribbean and nearby waters .</li><li>Regional posture: News outlets say the United States has built up a larger military presence in the Caribbean in recent months as part of counter‑narcotics operations .</li><li>Announcement method: Defence secretary Pete Hegseth relayed key details about the strike via a social‑media post, rather than only through formal Pentagon briefings, according to reporting .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>US Department of Defense / Pete Hegseth: Hegseth said the vessel was operated by a U.S.‑designated terrorist organisation and announced the strike publicly, describing the target as linked to narcotics trafficking. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/02/nx-s1-5594753/us-strike-caribbean-kills-3-drug-smugglers'>NPR</a>)</li><li>President Trump / White House: Reports say the operation was carried out on the President&#x27;s orders and described the targets as &#x27;narco‑terrorists&#x27; in official statements. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/2/us-military-kills-three-in-another-strike-on-caribbean-vessel'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>United Nations: The UN has urged Washington to halt such attacks, expressing concern about their continuation in the Caribbean region. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/us-launches-new-strike-on-alleged-narco-trafficking-boat/a-74588892'>Deutsche Welle</a>)</li><li>Russia: Moscow denounced the strikes as &#x27;excessive&#x27; and publicly backed Venezuela amid rising tensions over US operations in the Caribbean. (<a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/russia-denounces-%27excessive%27-us-military-force-in-caribbean-backs-venezuela'>Japan Today</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/nov/02/three-killed-in-us-military-strike-on-alleged-drug-vessel-in-the-caribbean'>Three killed in US military strike on alleged drug vessel in the Caribbean</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/02/nx-s1-5594753/us-strike-caribbean-kills-3-drug-smugglers'>US carries out new strike in Caribbean, killing 3 alleged drug smugglers</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/us-launches-new-strike-on-alleged-narco-trafficking-boat/a-74588892'>US launches new strike on alleged narco-trafficking boat</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/2/us-military-kills-three-in-another-strike-on-caribbean-vessel'>US military kills three in another strike on Caribbean vessel</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/three-killed-in-us-strike-on-alleged-drug-trafficking-boat-pentagon-confirms-13947096.html'>Three killed in US strike on alleged drug-trafficking boat, Pentagon confirms</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1om7ihh/us_military_kills_three_in_strike_on/'>US military kills three in strike on drug-trafficking ve